1: Download the files.
2. Seed the files.
3. Unpack the files using winrar or whatever.
4. When unpacked, you have a .img file.
5. If you wish to burn, use nero, imgburn or whatever. 
6. If you wish to watch it from harddrive, use daemon tools to mount the .img file and enjoy the file.
7. Seed some more.
